                    "created": "2010-06-09T08:52:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-09T08:52:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40925",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=leofzs",
                        "name": "leofzs",
                        "displayName": "Leonardo Fanzeres",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You don't need to use the empty form more than once for the same form. The new hash will be validated the same way as the generated on the first attempt. All the validation will be done on the form controller, and after the first attempt Ajax retrieves the hash value from the Json response and set it to the hash input.\r\n\r\nIf you still need more explanation, post some code, so I can understand better your doubt.",
